                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "Written to `journal/icon-audit.md`. Here's what it covers:\n\n**What the system uses:**\n- No icon library at all — no Font Awesome, Heroicons, Lucide, nothing loaded via CDN or npm\n- ~20 distinct hand-coded inline SVG shapes (all 24×24 stroke icons, matching Heroicons Outline style)\n- ~25 distinct emoji for categories, status, UI affordances\n- Unicode symbols (`✓` `✕` `✗` `⟳` `★` `☆`) for feedback and ratings\n\n**Key duplication problems:**\n- The checkmark SVG is copy-pasted in 5 places with inconsistent sizes\n- The pencil/edit SVG appears in 4 places\n- The search magnifier is in 4 templates\n- `🛍️` bag emoji is in 6 templates\n- `★` star rating logic is duplicated across 5+ templates\n\n**Standardisation path:** The doc recommends Django template partials for SVGs, and notes that all existing SVG shapes already match Heroicons Outline exactly — so adopting it would be a straight swap."
                  }
