                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "Understood. Here's what I'm going to do:\n\n**Setup (Step 1)**\n- Install `@phosphor-icons/core` via npm to get the actual SVG paths\n- Build `static/icons/sprite.svg` with all ~55 symbols from Section 5 (Fill weight, plus `star-regular`)\n- Create `templatetags/icon_tags.py` with `{% icon %}` and `{% sprite %}` tags\n- Add `{% sprite %}` to `base.html` after `<body>`\n- Add the base icon CSS\n\n**Replace inline SVGs (Steps 2–3)**\n- All duplicated SVGs in dashboard and store templates replaced with `{% icon \"...\" %}`\n- Sidebar in `base_dashboard.html`, nav in `base.html`\n\n**Replace emoji UI affordances (Step 4)**\n- `👁` `🙈` `✓` `✕` `✗` `⟳` `⚠` — all replaced with icon tags\n\n**Replace decorative emoji (Step 5)**\n- All commerce, contact, analytics emoji replaced\n\n**Category model (Step 6)**\n- Add `icon_name` field to `Category` model + migration\n- Update all 6 category section templates to use `{% icon category.icon_name %}`\n\n**Star ratings (Step 7)**\n- `★`/`☆` replaced across `_product_card.html`, `product_detail.html`, `testimonials_v1.html`, `hero_v1/v2/v3.html`\n\n**Homepage editor (Step 8)**\n- All editor-specific emoji and text affordances replaced\n\n**What I will NOT change:**\n- The `4.8★` stat strings in hero sections (those are data values from `store_settings`, not UI icons — they'd need a model change outside this scope)\n- County emoji in analytics (`🏙` `🌿`) — those are inside a Django template conditional on `address_county` values; I'll replace them\n- The `spec/` HTML files — those are prototypes, not live templates\n\nOne question before I proceed: the spec says to add `icon_name` to `Category` in `apps/store/models.py` — but looking at the codebase, `Category` is actually in `apps/products/models.py`. I'll put it there. Confirm and I'll start."
